<P>
<P><H2>World Congress Against Commercial Sexual Exploitation of Children</H2></TD><TD ALIGN=RIGHT>
<P><IMG src="122_1.gif"></TD></TR></TABLE>

<P><H2>ECPAT</H2><BR>
ECPAT was established in Bangkok in 1991, by a community of concerned individuals and organisations to work together to end child prostitution in Asin tourism. It campaigned for 3 years, working on political action, changes in the law, education and media coverage. There are currently over 250 groups in the coalitions which form the ECPAT network, in over 25 countries worldwide. <BR>

<P>ECPAT continues to campaign for action by governments in every country involved, and by the international community, to address this problem and protect all children. <BR>

<P><A HREF="http://www.rb.se/ecpat">Link to ECPAT</A>
