<h1 align="center"><font color="#0000A0">Distinctive Capabilities</font></h1>
<p align="center"><font color="#408080"><font size="4"><em>London
Economics is the leading British specialised economic
consultancy.</em> </font></font></p>
<div align="left">
<table border="2" width="100%">
    <tr>
        <td valign="top" width="50%">
        <h2><a href="compet.htm"><font color="#0000A0"><font
        size="4">Competition and Litigation Support </font></font></a></h2>
        <p align="left">LE provides expert assistance in cases
        involving UK and EC competition law, contractual and
        trade disputes, and many other areas of commercial law. </p>
        </td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
        <td width="50%">
        <h2><a href="internat.htm"><font color="#0000A0"><font
        size="4"><strong>International Experience</strong></font></font></a> </h2>
        <p><font size="3">LE now has experience of working in 52
        countries, particularly in the areas of energy
        (electricity and gas), water, telecommunications,
        macro-economics and environmental issues. A particular
        focus is in industrial restructuring, for example in
        Eastern Europe and the CIS countries.</font> </p>
        </td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
        <td>
        <h2><a href="strategy.htm"><font size="4">Strategy</font></a> </h2>
        <p><font size="3">Firms that succeed are those that
        understand where their real competitive advantage lies.
        By using sophisticated techniques to identify distinctive
        capabilities, London Economics helps companies make
        better pricing and investment decisions. A particular
        strength is the wide range of industries with which we
        have worked; this enables us to draw useful parallels
        with the client's experience. Our knowledge of the policy
        environment means we can also advise on where and how or
        prospective policies affect businesses.</font> </p>
        </td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
        <td width="50%">
        <h2><a href="energy.htm"><font color="#0000A0"><font
        size="4"><strong>Energy</strong></font></font></a><font
        color="#0000A0"><font size="4"><strong> </strong></font></font></h2>
        <p>LE offers a comprehensive range of strategic,
        regulatory and financial advice to companies, regulators
        and governments around the world concerned with
        electricity and gas. </p>
        </td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
        <td width="50%">
        <h2><a href="water.htm"><font size="4">Water</font></a> </h2>
        <p><font size="3">Privatisation and the new system of
        regulation has revolutionised the water industry in
        England and Wales. London Economics has been an advisor
        to the industry throughout these changes. We also advise
        governments and utilities around the world on water
        industry reform.</font> </p>
        </td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
        <td>
        <h2><a href="infrastr.htm"><font size="4">Infrastructure</font></a> </h2>
        <p><font size="3">The privatisation of key areas of
        transport and telecommunications infrastructure has
        created the need for regulation. London Economics is
        involved in the ongoing development of these regulatory
        systems and has advised companies, governments and
        regulatory bodies.</font> </p>
        </td>
    </tr>
</table>
</div>
