<h2>Web Changes</h2>
<hr>
<p>This is where we'll announce the most recent additions to our
web site. If you've visited us before and want to know what's
changed, take a look here first. </p>
<dl>
    <dt><img src="../images/smallnew.gif" align="bottom"
        width="35" height="22"> <strong>London Economics
        celebrates 10th anniversary. Read all about LE's progress
        from 1986 to 1996 in </strong><a
        href="../pubs/newslet/1996_4.htm"><strong>Economics in
        Action Issue 4</strong></a><strong>.</strong></dt>
    <dt>&#160;</dt>
</dl>
<h2>Press Releases</h2>
<hr>
<ul>
    <li>
        <h3><img src="../images/smallnew.gif" align="bottom"
        width="35" height="22"><a href="press1.htm">New Chairman
        as London Economics enters its second decade</a> </h3>
    </li>
</ul>
<blockquote>
    <h2><font size="3">London Economics, which celebrates its
    tenth anniversary on Monday, announced that </font><a
    href="sarahhog.htm"><font size="3">Sarah Hogg</font></a><font
    size="3"> would be succeeding John Kay as its Chairman with
    effect from January 1st, 1997.</font></h2>
</blockquote>
