    <li><font size="3">privatisation, restructuring and sector
        reform</font></li>
    <li><font size="3">regulation and legal frameworks</font></li>
    <li><font size="3">tariff studies and long term investment
        plans</font></li>
    <li><font size="3">financial and economic modelling</font></li>
    <li><font size="3">institutional strengthening and training</font></li>
    <li><font size="3">macro-economic analysis</font></li>
    <li><font size="3">environmental economics</font></li>
</ul>
<p align="left"><font size="3">We have worked in over 45
countries throughout Asia, Eastern Europe and the former Soviet
Union, Africa and Latin America. Projects are sometimes carried
out entirely with our own staff, and sometimes in association
with other professional firms covering areas such as engineering,
law and merchant banking.</font></p>
<p align="left">&#160;</p>
<h2 align="left"><font size="5">Key benefits</font></h2>
<p align="left"><font size="3">We apply rigorous economic
analysis, supported by the use of economic or financial models
where appropriate, to provide clear solutions to clients&#146;
problems. We have been extensively involved in the UK
privatisation process for electricity, gas and water are able to
draw on this expertise, as well as that in Australia and the US
where LE also has offices. However, we do not adhere to any fixed
model of industry structure and our wide international experience
ensures that we offer truly independent advice tailored to each
specific market.</font></p>
