<h1>Energy</h1>
<hr>
<h2>Services provided</h2>
<p>LE offers a comprehensive range of strategic, regulatory and
financial advice to companies, regulators and governments around
the world concerned with electricity and gas.</p>
<ul>
    <li>Corporate strategy in competitive energy markets and
        markets in transition</li>
    <li>Regulatory advice to clients on the scope, form and
        implementation of controls</li>
    <li>Preparation of cases to go before regulators and
        competition authorities</li>
    <li>Analysis and design of spot markets</li>
    <li>Evaluation and design of bulk electricity and gas
        contracts</li>
    <li>Preparation of market price scenarios</li>
    <li>Financial appraisal of investment opportunities</li>
    <li>Specialist advice in transmission pricing, regulatory
        price controls, pool modelling and risk management.</li>
</ul>
<h2>Key Benefits</h2>
<p>London Economics provides a global coverage of energy market
issues through our international network of offices. We also work
closely with many leading academic economists. This ensures that
we maintain a leading edge position in strategic thinking and
regulatory economics. As a result we are able to provide our
clients with analysis and expertise that either maximises their
competitive advantage or maximises economic benefits.</p>
