<html>
<head>
<title>Sarah Hogg</title>
<meta name="GENERATOR" content="Microsoft FrontPage 1.1">
<meta name="FORMATTER" content="Microsoft FrontPage 1.1">
</head>
<body background="../images/paper.jpg" text="#000080">
<h1>Sarah Hogg</h1>
<hr>
<p><font size="4">Sarah Hogg, who becomes Chairman of LE from
January 1997, began her career with The Economist, where she
became Economics Editor in 1977. After working for the <em>Sunday
Times,</em> <em>Channel 4 News</em> and <em>The Times</em> (where
she received the Wincott Award for Financial Journalist of the
Year), in 1986 she launched <em>The Independent's </em>award-winning
business section. After a spell writing for the<em> Daily </em>and <em>Sunday
Telegraph</em>, she was appointed Head of the Downing Street
Policy Unit in 1990, where she specialised in public sector
reform and international economic and trade issues. She joined LE
in 1995. </font></p>
<p><font size="4">Awarded a life peerage that year, she is also a
member of the House of Lords Science and Technology Committee.
She is on the Councils of the Royal Economic Society, the
Institute for Fiscal Studies and the Hansard Society. She is a
Director of NPI and the Foreign &amp; Colonial Smaller Companies
Trust, and has a number of international advisory positions.</font></p>
<hr>
<p>Copyright &#169; 1996 <strong>London Economics</strong><br>
</p>
