<title>Area Cost Adjustment Research Project</title>
<meta name="GENERATOR" content="Microsoft FrontPage 1.1">
<meta name="FORMATTER" content="Microsoft FrontPage 1.1">
</head>
<body background="../../images/backgrnd.jpg" text="#000080">
<h2><font color="#0000A0">Area Cost Adjustment Research Project A </font></h2>
<hr>
<h3><font color="#0000A0">Final Report</font></h3>
<p>To assist their review of the Area Cost Adjustment (ACA), the
Review Team has commissioned London Economics and its associates
Berkeley Hanover Consulting, Andrew Oswald and David
Blanchflower, to undertake Research Project A. While the other
research projects (B, C and D) were concerned with measuring the
extent of area labour cost variation and finding a more
theoretically robust methodology for the ACA, we have assessed
the practicality - as well as theoretical consistency - of the
many proposed methodologies and attempted to identify the best
one.</p>
<p>This is the final report for Research Project A. It provides
some discussion of the background to the ACA debate, both
theoretical and historical, classifies the various proposed
methodologies into groups and provides an assessment of each
group using the Review Team&#146;s criteria. We also make
reference to cases where specific proposals differ in significant
ways from other similar methodologies.<br>
<br>
